SPK_0: But I want to attempt to do quite a brave jump and maybe talk about the essence of a deal.

16
00:01:16,040 --> 00:01:18,380
SPK_0: So what lies in the essence of a deal?

17
00:01:18,540 --> 00:01:20,460
SPK_0: And yes, spoiler alert, it's in the title.

18
00:01:20,900 --> 00:01:27,420
SPK_0: It's this very interesting phrase, as if, or you can use like, synonyms.

19
00:01:29,240 --> 00:01:30,200
SPK_0: So what is the deal?

20
00:01:30,220 --> 00:01:36,220
SPK_0: And I will start with the quote, which I tried to find on this device, but it didn't want to give it to me.

21
00:01:36,300 --> 00:01:37,720
SPK_0: Well, which is interesting in itself.

22
00:01:37,780 --> 00:01:40,660
SPK_0: So we will have to rely on the quote from my head.

23
00:01:40,700 --> 00:01:43,520
SPK_0: And later I might put the perfect quote in the description.

24
00:01:43,720 --> 00:01:51,580
SPK_0: The quote belongs to a Spanish conservative, Juan de Noso de Cortes, who's been writing in the mid-19th century.

25
00:01:51,900 --> 00:01:54,760
SPK_0: And he gets this famous speech on dictatorship.

26
00:01:55,160 --> 00:01:57,160
SPK_0: I'm not going to quote the whole speech.

27
00:01:57,260 --> 00:01:59,380
SPK_0: I'm not even going to give the whole context.

28
00:02:00,220 --> 00:02:02,000
SPK_0: But I'm going to give this quote.

29
00:02:02,660 --> 00:02:04,720
SPK_0: The quote sounds like the following.

30
00:02:05,860 --> 00:02:11,300
SPK_0: And you will be like, as if, rich.

31
00:02:12,300 --> 00:02:18,120
SPK_0: That's the motto of the revolution of all low classes against nobility.

32
00:02:18,500 --> 00:02:19,360
SPK_1: Ah, okay.

33
00:02:19,560 --> 00:02:23,440
SPK_0: And you will be like, as if, aristocrats.

34
00:02:23,960 --> 00:02:29,140
SPK_0: That's the slogan of all the revolutions of merchants versus nobility.

35
00:02:30,220 --> 00:02:31,540
SPK_0: And you will be like kings.

36
00:02:32,360 --> 00:02:37,120
SPK_0: That's the motto of the revolution of all aristocrats against the king.

37
00:02:37,480 --> 00:02:38,920
SPK_0: And you will be like God.

38
00:02:39,720 --> 00:02:43,840
SPK_0: That's the motto of the first revolution, which happened before the creation of time.

39
00:02:45,280 --> 00:02:45,980
SPK_0: That's the quote.

40
00:02:47,220 --> 00:02:50,000
SPK_0: So you see how, I think it's an essence of the trick.

41
00:02:50,880 --> 00:02:53,980
SPK_0: And it comes directly to the will, to the self, to identity.

42
00:02:56,620 --> 00:02:58,360
SPK_0: Because what, and to technology.

43
00:02:58,720 --> 00:02:59,940
SPK_0: Like, it all comes down together.

44
00:03:01,200 --> 00:03:10,080
SPK_0: Because what the Gnostic deal offers you is an opportunity to be somebody without, what?

45
00:03:10,220 --> 00:03:12,880
SPK_0: Without bearing a cross of the somebody.

46
00:03:13,280 --> 00:03:17,540
SPK_0: That's what lies into, like, that's what lies into this, as if.

47
00:03:17,800 --> 00:03:18,200
SPK_1: Okay.

48
00:03:18,500 --> 00:03:23,980
SPK_0: Again, you take the part, in that case, the appearance, and present it as a whole.

49
00:03:24,220 --> 00:03:25,600
SPK_0: And it is very appealing.

50
00:03:25,940 --> 00:03:26,120
SPK_1: Aha.

51
00:03:26,860 --> 00:03:31,540
SPK_1: So we have maybe three recurring themes.

52
00:03:31,560 --> 00:03:38,600
SPK_1: One is the replacement of a real with a super salient simulation of the real.

53
00:03:39,520 --> 00:03:51,080
SPK_1: In this case, we have a second piece, which has to do with the ability to teleport or to invoke magic, let's say, sorcery.

54
00:03:51,080 --> 00:03:57,560
SPK_1: That instead of having the actual, the process that properly gives rise to the real.

55
00:03:57,640 --> 00:03:59,660
SPK_1: Because the real can only be born.

56
00:03:59,820 --> 00:04:01,320
SPK_1: The real can only grow the way.

57
00:04:01,560 --> 00:04:06,240
SPK_1: But the real grows, let's say, properly or naturally, the way that it has been designed, from the seed.

58
00:04:06,320 --> 00:04:09,640
SPK_1: If you wanted to eat real corn, you must plant real corn seed.

59
00:04:09,720 --> 00:04:11,840
SPK_1: And it must grow through the process of becoming a real corn.

60
00:04:12,180 --> 00:04:14,920
SPK_1: If you do something other than that, you do not, in fact, have real corn.

61
00:04:16,220 --> 00:04:18,920
SPK_1: But you can just use a very coarse example.

62
00:04:19,380 --> 00:04:20,980
SPK_1: I'll replace the corn now with an apple.

63
00:04:21,180 --> 00:04:28,220
SPK_1: There is the rare child who actually has not, on occasion, pulled a fake apple off of decor, which looks like an apple.

64
00:04:28,300 --> 00:04:31,080
SPK_1: It has made these super salient aspects of the visible.

65
00:04:31,600 --> 00:04:36,720
SPK_1: And really, really aptly, the young child reaches out and grabs it, begins to notice something is wrong initially.

66
00:04:36,880 --> 00:04:37,720
SPK_1: And it feels wrong.

67
00:04:37,720 --> 00:04:38,560
SPK_1: It's not got the right weight.

68
00:04:38,620 --> 00:04:39,780
SPK_1: And, of course, you get to try to bite it.

69
00:04:39,800 --> 00:04:40,480
SPK_1: It's not a real apple.

70
00:04:40,600 --> 00:04:40,900
SPK_1: Okay.

71
00:04:41,320 --> 00:04:42,300
SPK_1: So there's two things.

72
00:04:42,460 --> 00:04:53,200
SPK_1: One is I can give you a super salient simulation by foregrounding the elements that you are most able to perceive and might value in the lowest discerning way.

73
00:04:54,080 --> 00:05:01,280
SPK_1: And I can skip all of the suffering, all of the work, all of the durée, all of the investment, all of the condition, all of the...

74
00:05:02,520 --> 00:05:06,800
SPK_1: ...participation that is necessary for the production of the wheel and giving it to you, which is a pretty good deal.

75
00:05:07,260 --> 00:05:09,480
SPK_0: I just want to highlight there is an interesting part.

76
00:05:09,940 --> 00:05:13,140
SPK_0: It's not just about the process of becoming this as if.

77
00:05:13,660 --> 00:05:23,620
SPK_0: Because you can say that, let's say, a revolutionary, not doing magic, of course, just following the laws of dialectics, is ready for a lot of suffering in a process.

78
00:05:23,940 --> 00:05:27,700
SPK_0: You cannot just completely, like, it would be easier if they wouldn't.

79
00:05:27,880 --> 00:05:30,160
SPK_0: I mean, how many people would like, we know all of these revolutions.

80
00:05:30,500 --> 00:05:31,460
SPK_0: It's the reason why they are.

81
00:05:31,560 --> 00:05:32,740
SPK_0: I'm not capable of it, it's another question.

82
00:05:32,940 --> 00:05:36,640
SPK_0: Like, in my opinion, it's because good faculty are used in a different way.

83
00:05:36,740 --> 00:05:38,080
SPK_0: But let's put it this way, they're capable.

84
00:05:38,660 --> 00:05:46,220
SPK_0: But the idea of the deal is that once you hit this certain point, once you hit this point, for any future time,

85
00:05:46,440 --> 00:05:52,640
SPK_0: there will be no continuation of something you don't want to be part of this identity, effectively.

86
00:05:53,060 --> 00:06:00,840
SPK_0: And in that case, for example, to me, as a political philosopher, the easiest example is the whole anti-monarchic,

87
00:06:01,560 --> 00:06:05,040
SPK_0: radical revolution of aristocracy, because ultimately it's a very simple idea.

88
00:06:05,160 --> 00:06:08,660
SPK_0: Can I have the privileges of aristocracy without having to serve?

89
00:06:09,120 --> 00:06:09,560
SPK_1: Right.

90
00:06:10,380 --> 00:06:10,820
SPK_0: Anymore.

91
00:06:10,880 --> 00:06:11,260
SPK_0: Right.

92
00:06:11,340 --> 00:06:15,820
SPK_0: So it's in process of getting this right not to serve, I'm capable of many sacrifices.

93
00:06:16,040 --> 00:06:18,020
SPK_0: I can even go and fight for it.

94
00:06:18,100 --> 00:06:19,480
SPK_0: But once I get there, can I stop?

95
00:06:19,600 --> 00:06:21,220
SPK_0: Like, can you give it me away?

96
00:06:21,440 --> 00:06:27,020
SPK_1: Yes, I think maybe the way of bridging is to say that the concept isn't ultimately down to suffering.

97
00:06:27,160 --> 00:06:27,420
SPK_1: Yes.

98
00:06:27,460 --> 00:06:31,540
SPK_1: As much as it is down to participating in the actual process.

99
00:06:31,560 --> 00:06:31,820
SPK_1: Yes.

100
00:06:31,820 --> 00:06:32,420
SPK_1: Of the thing.

101
