112
00:06:57,540 --> 00:06:57,860
SPK_1: Yes.

113
00:06:57,960 --> 00:06:59,020
SPK_1: So I want to be the king.

114
00:06:59,460 --> 00:07:01,120
SPK_1: Well, in reality, you are not the king.

115
00:07:01,560 --> 00:07:02,520
SPK_1: Well, fuck that.

116
00:07:03,340 --> 00:07:06,160
SPK_1: I want to go to the grocery store and I want to be able to pay money.

117
00:07:06,260 --> 00:07:10,720
SPK_1: I'm willing to work really hard to get the coin to buy the identity of king.

118
00:07:10,820 --> 00:07:12,940
SPK_1: But if I want king, I want king.

119
00:07:13,240 --> 00:07:17,800
SPK_1: And we're saying in reality, the notion that reality actually has a reality of its own.

120
00:07:17,900 --> 00:07:19,000
SPK_0: There is tyranny of name.

121
00:07:19,320 --> 00:07:20,500
SPK_1: The tyranny of name.

122
00:07:20,620 --> 00:07:21,500
SPK_1: This is anathema.

123
00:07:21,680 --> 00:07:22,720
SPK_1: So that's the key.

124
00:07:22,760 --> 00:07:23,760
SPK_1: I get both.

125
00:07:24,100 --> 00:07:28,800
SPK_1: I get this super salient simulacrum, but I also get the triumph of the will.

126
00:07:28,920 --> 00:07:30,520
SPK_0: You get your triumph of the will.

127
00:07:30,580 --> 00:07:30,860
SPK_0: Yes.

128
00:07:30,860 --> 00:07:31,440
SPK_0: Yes, absolutely.

129
00:07:31,700 --> 00:07:32,980
SPK_0: It comes to the triumph of the will.

130
00:07:33,780 --> 00:07:38,780
SPK_0: And this triumph is exactly, again, comes back to the point of the tyranny of the name.

131
00:07:38,940 --> 00:07:41,700
SPK_0: I don't have to be tyrannical to my name.

132
