SPK_0: Now, noble means to have X amount of income or to have a certain lineage or to do a certain thing.

138
00:07:59,320 --> 00:07:59,480
SPK_0: Right.

139
00:08:00,860 --> 00:08:03,740
SPK_0: You're taking a part of it through your, exactly, through your will.

140
00:08:03,840 --> 00:08:10,600
SPK_0: And again, in doing this, you are capable of many sacrifices, but it's sacrifices to ultimately to whom?

141
00:08:10,620 --> 00:08:11,420
SPK_0: To your own will.

142
00:08:11,680 --> 00:08:12,040
SPK_1: Yes.

143
00:08:12,680 --> 00:08:13,520
SPK_1: This is the key.

144
00:08:13,540 --> 00:08:13,880
SPK_1: Exactly.

145
00:08:14,260 --> 00:08:15,420
SPK_1: Sacrifices to your own will.

146
00:08:15,500 --> 00:08:21,380
SPK_1: And on the basis of sacrifices that at the end of the day, you are willing to make and you can make.

147
00:08:21,460 --> 00:08:23,120
SPK_1: At the point of the tyranny of the name.

148
00:08:23,520 --> 00:08:30,480
SPK_1: And I actually kind of like that because it was, I will accept the propaganda and just make it something that I,

149
00:08:30,860 --> 00:08:37,800
SPK_1: and noble, the point of the tyranny of the name is that there may be no sacrifice you can make because this is simply not yours.

150
00:08:38,060 --> 00:08:39,520
SPK_1: It's that are all, there's all this.

